---
import CTAButton from "../ui/CTAButton.astro";
import NavigationHint from "../ui/NavigationHint.astro";
---

<!-- Legacy Section -->
<section
  id="legacy"
  class="snap-none-mobile pt-24 pb-20 md:py-20 md:min-h-[100dvh] flex flex-col px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex-1 flex flex-col justify-center">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-16">
      What you leave behind
    </h2>
    <div
      class="prose prose-lg sm:prose-xl prose-invert max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12"
    >
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
        What you know deep down is important — and not just for you. Drawn out,
        given voice, your reserves of knowledge can become something you carry
        forward with you and something you leave behind.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
        We're talking about a non-monetary legacy. Through extended philosophic
        conversation — sometimes over many months and dozens of sessions —
        what's buried is drawn to the surface and formulated in your own voice.
        The sense that you had something to say becomes something said.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
        At the beginning of things, at the end of things, in retirement, after a
        marriage has fallen apart, at the death of a loved one, when you're
        changing careers. At certain points in your life you can see forward and
        backward with unusual clarity. Accumulated experience meets the
        willingness to reckon with what it all amounts to. That vantage point is
        rare and precious and won't always be available in quite this same way —
        which makes it an especially good time to do this work.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300">
        Each conversation, if you choose, produces artifacts — audio recordings
        and crafted transcripts that become part of your library. The tangible
        form of what you're building: something to return to, to build on, to
        share, ultimately to leave behind.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Let's talk CTA -->
    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <CTAButton variant="secondary" />
    </div>

    <NavigationHint href="#process" text="What to expect" />
  </div>
</section>
